1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a framework for generating cache-oblivious layouts for binary search trees, which falls under the domain of data structures. 
2. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses cache misses and their impact on hierarchical memory, which is related to hardware architecture. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the effect of cache misses on performance, which is relevant to distributed and parallel computing. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper introduces a new locality measure and investigates the relative effect of different decisions in constructing cache-oblivious layouts, which is related to computational complexity. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper proposes a framework for generating cache-oblivious layouts, which could be implemented in programming languages.
